<subSubSection id="C33A654647326051E080FF581A49FF31" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9F36CD47326051E080FF581A49FF31" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E080FF58190BFF55" bold="true" box="[189,356,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D4E47326051E1D5FF581A1EFF55" authorityName="Z. Wang, P. P. Wu &amp; S. X. Yu" authorityYear="2022" box="[488,625,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nushanensis">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E1D5FF581A1EFF55" box="[488,625,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">nushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the 
<typeStatus id="549B886F47326051E33CFF591B5EFF54" box="[769,817,159,185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">type</typeStatus>
locality, Nushan Mountain, and the Chinese name of this new species is given as 怒Ɯ凤Njffi.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A654647326051E080FF20188DFE81" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9F36CD47326051E080FF201C34FEED" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,545]" box="[189,1115,230,257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E080FF201930FEED" bold="true" box="[189,351,230,256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Flowering from July to August and fruiting from August to October.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36CD47326051E080FECC188DFE81" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E080FECC1A66FEC9" bold="true" box="[189,521,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Ecology and distribution:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C204D4E47326051E234FECD1B68FEC9" authorityName="Z. Wang, P. P. Wu &amp; S. X. Yu" authorityYear="2022" box="[521,775,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nushanensis">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E234FECD1B68FEC9" box="[521,775,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Impatiens nushanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in shady areas on mountain slope in open fragmented coniferous forests at elevations of 
<quantity id="4CD89B2847326051E23EFEE81ACFFEA4" box="[515,672,302,329]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" unit="m" value="3250.0" valueMax="3300.0" valueMin="3200.0">3200–3300 m</quantity>
. It is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F82F47326051E365FEE91C75FEA5" box="[856,1050,302,329]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
. For now, it is found only in the 
<typeStatus id="549B886F47326051E546FEE91DC4FEA4" box="[1403,1451,303,329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A654647326051E080FEB01C5CFDCD" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B9F36CD47326051E080FEB01C5CFDCD" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B954EADF47326051E080FEB019A0FE7D" bold="true" box="[189,463,374,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
Only three populations composed of about 400 individuals in total are found. The habitat area is less than 
<quantity id="4CD89B2847326051E107FE5C19EFFE59" box="[314,384,410,436]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C559B8547326051E1BDFE5C19E7FE45" attach="left" box="[384,392,410,424]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="192">2</superScript>
, but the microhabitat and microclimate nearby are highly similar. For the time being, the habitat is beyond the interference of human activities, and the populations are without a decline trend. Thus, we propose to categorize the species as Vulnerable (VU D2), following the International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources guidelines (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B3C47326051E1E2FDC01C48FDCD" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[479,1063,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="192" refId="ref2844" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2022) Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 15. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: https: // nc. iucnredlist. org / redlist / content / attachment _ files / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed January 2022)" type="book" year="2022">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
